$ /etc/resolv.conf

`/etc/resolv.conf` is the resolver configuration file. It's used to access the → development/networking/DNS[DNS] (domain name service).

The following simple exmample content specifies the nameserver to be 8.8.8.8:
code {
nameserver 8.8.8.8
code }

? At least in → Linux/distributions/Ubuntu, /etc/resolv.conf is not used anymore, unless its »manually« implemented.

sa:
  → Linux/shell/commands/host[`host`]
